</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen" box="[199,393,188,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1995) Infraorder Gerromorpha Popov, 1971 - semiaquatic bugs, pp. 17 - 114. In: Aukema, B. &amp; Rieger, C. (Eds.), Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. Vol. 1. Enicocephalomorpha, Dipsocoromorpha, Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha and Leptopodomorpha. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Amsterdam, xxvi + 222 pp." type="book chapter" year="1995">Andersen (1995)</bibRefCitation>
interpreted the distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[766,927,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liliimacula">
<emphasis box="[766,927,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">H. liliimacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as ‘Transcaucasia’ and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[1219,1436,188,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (1997) Hebridae of Russia and adjacent countries (Heteroptera). Zoosystematica Rossica, 6, 223 - 236." type="journal article" year="1997">Kanyukova (1997)</bibRefCitation>
expected its distribution in Armenia or Azerbaijan. However, examination of rich material of 
<taxonomicName box="[1244,1327,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1244,1327,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Hebrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Caucasus, Turkey and Iran did not led to rediscovery of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[916,1113,260,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (1997) Hebridae of Russia and adjacent countries (Heteroptera). Zoosystematica Rossica, 6, 223 - 236." type="journal article" year="1997">Kanyukova 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[1124,1183,260,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Vodnye poluzhestkokrylye nasekomye (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauny Rossii i sopredelnykh stran. [Aquatic and semiaquatic (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) of the fauna of Russia and neighbouring countries]. Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, 296 pp. [in Russian, English abstract]" type="book" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kment" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Kment, P. &amp; Kanyukova, E. V. (2010) New faunistic records of Hebridae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) from the Mediterranean, Near and Middle East. Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae, 95 (2), 11 - 18." type="journal article" year="2010">Kment &amp; Kanyukova 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fent" box="[221,400,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Fent, M., Kment, P., Camur-Elipek, B. &amp; Kirgiz, T. (2011) Annotated catalogue of Enicocephalomorpha, Dipsocoromorpha, Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha and Leptopodomorpha (Hemiptera: Heteroptera) of Turkey with new records. Zootaxa, 2856, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2011">
Fent 
<emphasis box="[278,335,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1290989270" collectorName="H. Leder. The" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="syntype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,332,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Comment.</emphasis>
This species with characteristic ‘lilly-shaped’ whitish pattern on the membrane was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Horvath" box="[151,325,367,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Horvath, G. (1929) Species novae Hebridarum (Hem. Het.) in Museo Nationali Hungarico asservata. Annales Historico- Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 26, 313 - 317." type="journal article" year="1929">Horváth (1929)</bibRefCitation>
based on male and female 
<typeStatus box="[634,732,368,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">syntypes</typeStatus>
from the Caucasus collected by 
<collectorName box="[1102,1260,367,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">H. Leder. The</collectorName>
species has not been collected since. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[398,611,404,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (1997) Hebridae of Russia and adjacent countries (Heteroptera). Zoosystematica Rossica, 6, 223 - 236." type="journal article" year="1997">Kanyukova (1997)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed and keyed the species based on a single female originating from the same series as the 
<typeStatus box="[479,581,440,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">syntypes</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
. Proper description of the male is therefore missing. Checking for a male syntype within the type series deposited in HNHM might shed new light on this problem.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
